          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "A Virtual Machine requires its own full Guest Operating System (e.g., Windows or Linux) on top of a hypervisor, making it heavy and slow to boot. A container shares the Host OS kernel, isolating only the application and its dependencies, making it lightweight and fast."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is Docker?",
